events.name: Sierra Leone Google Developer Group Meetup
events.description:
Meet with other developers in the Sierra Leonean tech environment as they share ideas and network with each other. Discussions during the meet-up would mostly be about technological solutions for health in West Africa especially in the Risk Communication sector. This would serve as the breeding ground for fresh ideas for the Hackathon competition on Risk Communication for West Africa which would take place at the same location from the 28th - 31st May, 2018.

Don't miss out, join us at Sensi Tech Innovation Hub on Thursday at 4:30pm and be part of this unique meet-up.

events.name: GDG FREETOWN (WORKING WITH GOOGLE DRIVE)
events.description:
Meet with other developers in the Sierra Leonean tech environment as they share ideas and network with each other. We will be exploring one of the Google products (GOOGLE DRIVE). We will be looking at features of the GOOGLE DRIVE and how we can apply its usage in our everyday lives.

Don't miss out, join us at Sensi Tech Innovation Hub on Thursday at 4:30pm and be part of this unique meet-up.

events.name: GOOGLE I/O EXTENDED FREETOWN
events.description:
Too tired to stay up all night to watch the Google I/O keynote? Don't worry – we've got you covered.
Join us for a screening of the keynote, and hear all about the key announcements from Google.

I/O Extended events include a variety of options for developers—from live streaming sessions to local demos, hackathons, codelabs, and more. Food and drink will be provided, and there will be plenty of time to network with other people in the industry.

Time: Doors open at 10:30pm, Keynote begins at 11:00pm, First Android App Bundle Kicks Off at 4:30pm

Timetable (time and schedule subject to change):

10:30pm - Doors Open

11:00pm - 1:00pm - Keynote live streamed.

1:00pm - 2:30pm - Dinner (provided), Networking, and Workshop set-up

4:30pm - 4:30pm - First Android App Bundle.

events.name: Sierra Leone Google Developers Meetup ( Cloud Platform )
events.description:
Meet with developers and techie form the Sierra Leone tech ecosystem as they share unique and new ideas about the Google cloud platform and have the opportunity to network with each other.

Discussions during the meet-up would mostly be about utilizing the Google Cloud system effectively for a better result, Google Cloud systems like Google Firebase, Google Database, Google APIs, Google Storage, Google Docs and many more will be discussed.

Don't miss out, join us at Sensi Tech Innovation Hub on Friday at 4:30 pm and be part of this unique meet-up.

group_profile.intro: We work with Google to help grow a tech innovation community in Sierra Leone.We use the resources available through this community to organise activities   and events educating a new generation.
